  whitepaper was that ~80% of the current vape industry's revenue goes to wholesalers and distributors, not producers. 

Why? Producers are not allowed to advertise on social media and have to rely on such third parties. The result? Consumers always pay a big premium.

Puff Paw’s solution to all of the above

PuffPaw's smart vape system incorporates a proprietary encrypted chip in both the vape device and e-liquid pods, enabling real-time tracking of user behavior (including puff timing, frequency, and duration) through Bluetooth connectivity to a mobile app while ensuring product authenticity through encrypted anti-counterfeiting codes stored on-chain. 

In simple terms, you know exactly how much nicotine you’re taking in.

Puffpaw e-liquids contain organic components, such as tea extracts (also present in everyday food additives). 

This strategy seeks to provide a vaping experience that is at least ten times better than that of current goods.

Despite perhaps greater production costs, Puffpaw anticipates offering competitive pricing for its enhanced vaping experience. Since they don’t rely on third party distributors, I can see that being very feasible.
Game theory

With each puff, Puffpaw users receive $VAPE, the native token. Consumers who use e-liquids with less nicotine gain more tokens and the top earners are users who switch to the non-nicotine vape, Puffpaw’s primary offering. 

In this manner, smokers are progressively encouraged to reduce their nicotine all the way down to zero. Importantly, a user can only acquire a certain quantity of tokens every day. Capping these rewards is beneficial both both user and token health.

Okay, let’s hold on for a second. Do you remember STEPN? The running game that literally took off in the 2021 bull run? Well, Puff Paw reminds me of this in many ways by the way they gamify this experience.

How do you use it?

Step 1 is to mint a “PUFF PASS” (NFT). You will then receive your physical vape and can access the Puffpaw APP (powered by Privy) which has the Vape To Earn gamification function.

All vaping activity and earned rewards are recorded on-chain, giving users a transparent and secure record of their progress. 

Only PUFF PASS holders can earn token rewards. I also asked myself why they called the NFT a PUFF PASS. 

Apparently there's slang used by smokers who share a blunt, where they “puff puff” and then they “pass” it on. 

Personally I don’t smoke nor vape, so I am going to do something else: lending. Lenders can hold PUFF PASS NFTs and lease their vape out to other people (borrowers). 

Puffpaw has over 2,000 KYC-verified borrowers available for PUFF PASS owners to lend their vapes at 90%/10% profit sharing ratio. 

Note: unless you have a whitelist, you can only mint a PUFF PASS NFT after December 9 (only 10,000 available initially, no information whether there will be another sale this year or if the price will increase in future).

Some closing thoughts

So as with STEPN where you earned GMT for jogging daily, here you will earn $VAPE tokens based on how you use the product (or rent it out). Is the token sustainable?

Unlike STEPN, there’s two big revenue streams here: selling physical products (vapes, e-liquids, upcoming products) and data monetization (anonymous, with user’s consent). 

As long as there is demand for and usage of the vapes, unprecedented health data will be collected that I imagine big companies would pay for - and hopefully it will save medical research some years and money too. 

More vapes sold → more users → more health data → more data consumers → More $VAPE incentives.
